<plot>The inexperienced documentary maker Alfredo Locane gets the opportunity of his life when he is invited to interview Maury Kubrick. Maury is the younger brother of the famous director Stanley Kubrick and he is about to publish his memoirs. Maury is a strange person however. He breaks down every minute and gets strange phone calls about being fired. His story seems interesting though, he tells about his fishing trips with Stanley and the one time he saved Neil Diamond from drowning. But the film crew gets suspicious and starts searching for the real truth. Is Maury really who he tells he is?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?008654</url></doc>
